  "texts": [
    "This unsupervised model combines autoencoder-based reconstruction with adversarial training to generate high-quality graph representations.",
    "The AGAE loss function is defined as follows:",
    "where G(⋅) represents the generator, and D(⋅) signifies the discriminator.",
    "The discriminator's role is to distinguish between the real input graph, p z, and the reconstructed graph generated by the generator G(F, X).",
    "Graph Attentional Autoencoder (GAAE) (Salehi and Davulcu 2019) is a variant of graph autoencoders that combines Graph Attention Network (GAT) with GAE."
